1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/?p=130644";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:176:"WordPress 4.0 Beta 1 is out, what it''s like working for a distributed company and lots of weekend projects.\r\n\r\nCheck out The Whip for more daily lashings of WordPress goodness.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"The WhiP Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15322:"<div class="image-grid cgrid-row">\n<div class="cgrid-col cgrid-col-span-full"><a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the_whip.jpg" rel="lightbox[130644]" title="The WhiP Newsletter #40"><img class="aligncenter size-ratio-large wp-image-129574" src="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the_whip-700x192.jpg" alt="The WhiP" width="700" height="192" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<p>Hello lovely reader!</p>\n<p><strong>WordPress 4.0.</strong>Beta 1 has been released for testing.<a href="http://wordpress.org/news/2014/07/wordpress-4-0-beta-1/" target="_blank">Check out the announcement</a>for a full rundown of upcoming features.</p>\n<p><strong>Theres lots of other news!</strong>Akismet 3.0.1<a href="http://blog.akismet.com/2014/07/10/akismet-3-0-1-for-wordpress-now-available/" target="_blank">has been released</a>, the<a href="http://wptavern.com/wordpress-mini-conference-east-meets-press-set-for-september-17-21-2014" target="_blank">East Meets Press mini conference</a>will be held in September, and Nantes in France will host<a href="http://2014.wptech.fr/" target="_blank">WP tech for developers</a>only in November.</p>\n<p><strong>Working for a distributed company.</strong>Automattic VIP Global Services Manager Sara Ross has written<a href="http://whenihavetime.com/2014/07/08/10-lessons-from-4-years-working-remotely/" target="_blank">10 lessons shes learnt after four years working remotely</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Its all about managed web hosting.</strong><a href="http://torquemag.io/dradcast-episode-050-godfather-pressnomics/" target="_blank">Pagely CEO Josh Strebel</a>features on this weeks episode of Dradcast, while Flywheel founder Dusty Davidson<a href="http://mattreport.com/dusty-davidson-flywheel/" target="_blank">talks about starting his business in a closest</a>on the Matt Report.</p>\n<p><strong>Promoting a young premium plugin.</strong>Tom Ewer<a href="https://managewp.com/promoting-premium-plugin" target="_blank">talks to the team behind WP Rocket</a>, a commercial caching plugin.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>How many plugins is too many plugins?</strong>The<a href="http://webdesignledger.com/tools/15-must-have-wordpress-plugins-for-2014" target="_blank">15 must-have plugins for 2014</a>, according to Web Design Ledger. iThemes has released a sync app that allows you to<a href="http://ithemes.com/2014/07/10/new-ithemes-sync-iphone-app/" target="_blank">update your WordPress sites from your iOS device</a>. Plus, WP Lift reviews the<a href="http://wplift.com/contact-form-plugins-for-wordpress" target="_blank">best contact form plugins for WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutorials, how-tos, distractions etc.</strong>If you find yourself constantly explaining the difference between WordPress.org and WordPress.com to clients and friends, youll want to<a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/wordpress-org-vs-wordpress-com-a-definitive-guide-for-2014/" target="_blank">bookmark our definitive guide</a>on the WPMU DEV Blog. Sitepoint has a published a handy guide to<a href="http://www.sitepoint.com/optimizing-wordpress-performance-with-p3" target="_blank">optimizing WordPress with the P3 plugin</a>. The folks at The Edublogger have put together an<a href="http://theedublogger.com/2014/07/09/the-ultimate-directory-of-free-image-sources/" target="_blank">awesome collection of free image resources</a>. Find out<a href="http://www.elegantthemes.com/blog/tips-tricks/how-to-create-wordpress-custom-fields" target="_blank">how to create custom fields</a>at Elegant Themes. Lastly, WP Beginner explains<a href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-create-a-web-directory-in-wordpress/" target="_blank">how to create a web directory in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Advanced how-tos.</strong>Tuts+ runs you through<a href="http://code.tutsplus.com/tutorials/using-the-tgm-plugin-activation-library-in-your-themes--cms-20901" target="_blank">using the TGM plugins activation library in your themes</a>. And Tom McFarlin shows you how to<a href="http://tommcfarlin.com/writing-javascript-helpers-wordpress-theme-customizer/" target="_blank">write JavaScript helpers for the WordPress Theme Customizer</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Hello weekend!</strong>BIC, the company that created the ballpoint pen, has set out to<a href="http://theuniversaltypeface.com/" target="_blank">create a universal font</a>. Would you put money on a crocodile or a snake in a battle to the death? (<a href="http://www.iflscience.com/plants-and-animals/amazing-photographs-video-snake-devouring-crocodile" target="_blank">If you said snake, you win</a>). Dubai has revealed<a href="http://www.dezeen.com/2014/07/10/mall-of-the-world-dubai-first-climate-controlled-city/" target="_blank">plans for the worlds first indoor city</a>, complete with a temperature-controlled mega resort featuring a retractable glass roof and the worlds largest shopping centre. Surely its the stuff of nightmares.</p>\n<p>Have an awesome weekend!<br />\n		<!-- Begin MailChimp Signup Form -->\n		<link href="//cdn-images.mailchimp.com/embedcode/classic-081711.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">\n		<div id="mc_embe