out The Whip for more daily lashings of WordPress goodness.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"The WhiP Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14737:"<div class="image-grid cgrid-row">\n<div class="cgrid-col cgrid-col-span-full"><a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the_whip.jpg" rel="lightbox[130593]" title="The WhiP Newsletter #38"><img class="aligncenter size-ratio-large wp-image-129574" src="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the_whip-700x192.jpg" alt="The WhiP" width="700" height="192" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<p>Hello dear reader,</p>\n<p><strong>Happy birthday!</strong> <a title="We are six" href="http://www.woothemes.com/2014/07/six-years/" target="_blank">WooThemes turns six today</a> and is celebrating with 50 per cent off all products for 24 hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Awesome Motive deal.</strong>WP Beginners Syed Balkhi and Griffin Medias Thomas Griffin have<a href="http://www.poststat.us/syed-balkhi-thomas-griffin-awesome-motive" target="_blank">joined forces</a>. The pair originally teamed up to create<a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/floating-social-bar/" target="_blank">Floating Social Bar</a>and later<a href="http://optinmonster.com/" target="_blank">OptinMonster</a>. Thomas will join Syeds company Awesome Motive as CTO.</p>\n<p><strong>PHP vs Javascript.</strong>WordPress co-founder Matt Mullenweg reckons<a href="http://wptavern.com/in-the-next-few-years-90-of-wordpress-development-could-be-javascript-based" target="_blank">90 per cent of WordPress development could be Javascript in the next few years</a>, but a comparison of core code reveals PHP isnt disappearing from WordPress development any time soon.</p>\n<p><strong>Position vacant.</strong> Were looking for a Copywriter to join the Incsub team. If youre interested in the role or know someone who might be,<a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/come-copywrite-with-us/" target="_blank">get in touch</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Hofstadters law.</strong>WooThemess Dan Johnson, the lead developer for Sensei,<a href="http://www.woothemes.com/2014/07/lessons-learnt-planning-big-product-release/" target="_blank">imparts his lessons learnt</a>after planning the learning management software&#8217;s most recent release.</p>\n<p><strong>In other news</strong>Planning is underway on<a href="http://wptavern.com/wordpress-feature-plugin-planned-to-improve-image-editing-experience" target="_blank">improvements to the WordPress image editing experience</a>. Proposed Customizer improvements<a href="http://wptavern.com/proposed-customizer-improvements-for-wordpress-4-0-land-amid-concerns-over-underlying-architectural-problems" target="_blank">highlight underlying architectural issues</a>.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>WordPress projects.</strong>Use jQuery to<a href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-themes/how-to-fade-in-the-last-sidebar-widget-in-wordpress-using-jquery/" target="_blank">fade in the last sidebar widget in WordPress</a>. ManageWP shows you<a href="https://managewp.com/embed-live-google-plus-hangout-wordpress" target="_blank">how to embed a live Google+ Hangout</a>on your site. For the environmentally conscious, create a site with WordPress and the<a href="http://wplift.com/environmental-wordpress-theme" target="_blank">Eco Recycling Theme</a>. Lastly, find out how to<a href="http://torquemag.io/turning-your-website-into-a-mobile-app-with-apppresser/" target="_blank">turn your site into a mobile app with AppPresser</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Its time to stop ignoring other languages.</strong>With more than a third of WordPress installations now set up in languages other than English,<a href="http://www.poststat.us/automating-i18n-wordpress-themes/" target="_blank">it makes sense to localize your site</a>. Every developer should check out<a href="http://www.poststat.us/automating-i18n-wordpress-themes/" target="_blank">Brady Verchers handy guide to automating i18n in themes</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Read on if you like to procrastinate (or even if you don&#8217;t).</strong>Looking for a graphic designer?<a href="http://textastrophe.com/post/89883536350/the-graphic-designer" target="_blank">This guy might be for you.</a>The<a href="http://fortune.com/2014/07/07/arrillaga-silicon-valley/" target="_blank">secretive billionaire</a>who built Silicon Valley. And,<a href="http://lifehacker.com/four-methods-to-create-a-secure-password-youll-actually-1601854240" target="_blank">never forget your password again</a>.</p>\n<p>See you again tomorrow!</p>\n<p><span style="color: #04233d;">		<!-- Begin MailChimp Signup Form -->\n		<link href="//cdn-images.mailchimp.com/embedcode/classic-081711.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">\n		<div id="mc_embed_signup">\n		<form action="http://wpmudev.us1.list-manage.com/subscribe/post?u=53a1e972a043d1264ed082a5b&amp;id=74fb43fd55" method="post" id="mc-embedded-subscribe-form" name="mc-embedded-subscribe-form" class="validate" target="_blank" novalidate>\n		<h3>Subscribe to The WhiP</h3>\n		<div class="indicates-required"><span class="asterisk">*</span> indicates required</div>\n		<div class="mc-field-group">\n		<label for="mce-EMAIL">Email Address  <span class="asterisk">*</span>\n		</label>\n		<input type="email" value="" name="EMAIL" class="required email" id="mce-EMAIL">\n		</div>\n		<div id="mce-responses" class="clear">\n		<div class="response" id="mce-error-response" style="display:none"></div>\n		<div class="response" id="mce-success-response" style="display:none"></div>\n		</div>    <!-- real people should not fill this in and expect good things - do not remove this or risk form bot signups-->\n		   <div style="position: absolute; left: -5000px;"><input typ