:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"The WhiP Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5831:"<div class="image-grid cgrid-row">\n<div class="cgrid-col cgrid-col-span-full"><a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the_whip.jpg" rel="lightbox[130535]" title="The WhiP Newletter #37"><img class="aligncenter size-ratio-large wp-image-129574" src="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/the_whip-700x192.jpg" alt="The WhiP" width="700" height="192" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<p>And were back!</p>\n<p><strong>Birthday giveaway.</strong>WP Beginner is<a href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/wpbeginner-5th-birthday-giveaway-help-build-a-school/" target="_blank">celebrating its fifth birthday</a>with a<a href="http://wptavern.com/wpbeginner-turns-5-celebrates-with-campaign-to-build-two-new-schools-in-guatemala" target="_blank">campaign to build</a><a href="http://wptavern.com/wpbeginner-turns-5-celebrates-with-campaign-to-build-two-new-schools-in-guatemala" target="_blank">two schools in Guatemala</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>I18n.</strong>WordPress 4.0 will<a href="http://wptavern.com/wordpress-4-0-to-add-language-selection-to-installation" target="_blank">introduce major internationalisation improvements</a>, making it easier to set up and use the software in languages other than English.</p>\n<p><strong>WooUpgrade.</strong>WooThemes has<a href="http://www.woothemes.com/2014/07/wooframework-6-has-arrived/" target="_blank">released WooFramework 6</a>, which includesa large code rewrite.</p>\n<p><strong>Lots of opinions.</strong>Brian Krogsgard<a href="http://www.poststat.us/state-handling-custom-metadata-wordpress/" target="_blank">has his say</a>on the state of handling custom metadata in WordPress. Our very own Chris Knowles<a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/free-wordpress-themes-are-stunning-awesome-impressive-so-why-buy-one/" target="_blank">questions the logic in downloading free themes</a>. And while were talking about free stuff, Brenda Barron asks,<a href="https://managewp.com/free-wordpress-plugins" target="_blank">Are free plugins worth the effort?&#8221;</a><br />\n<br />\n<strong>The latest guides to WordPress.</strong><a href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/opinion/wordpress-vs-blogger-which-one-is-better-pros-and-cons/" target="_blank">WordPress or Blogger?</a>WP Beginner looks at the pros and cons. iThemes has a great<a href="http://ithemes.com/2014/07/07/how-wordpress-ecommerce-works/" target="_blank">headache-free guide to how WordPress eCommerce works</a>. If you use a lot of stock images, WP Lift has put together a<a href="http://wplift.com/free-stock-images" target="_blank">collection of free high-res stock image resources</a>. Plus, WooThemes has a<a href="http://www.woothemes.com/2014/07/e-commerce-customer-support/" target="_blank">guide to offering top-notch customer support</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>WordPress tutorials.</strong>Find out<a href="http://www.catswhocode.com/blog/how-to-build-a-fixed-menu-in-3-easy-steps" target="_blank">how to build a fixed menu in three easy steps</a>. Enable two-factor authentication on your site with<a href="http://www.wpexplorer.com/2-factor-authentication-wordpress/" target="_blank">this guide from WP Explorer</a>. And find out more about<a href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/showcase/3-best-affiliate-tracking-and-management-software-for-wordpress/" target="_blank">affiliate tracking and management software</a>for WordPress.</p>\n<p><strong>Advanced tutorials.</strong>Tuts+ runs you through<a href="http://code.tutsplus.com/tutorials/how-to-customize-the-wordpress-dashboard-to-minimize-confusion--cms-20344" target="_blank">how to customize the WordPress dashboard</a>. Its a great read if you want to simplify WordPress for clients. The site also features an article on<a href="http://code.tutsplus.com/tutorials/running-wordpress-on-openshift-an-introduction--cms-20058" target="_blank">running WordPress on OpenShift</a>. If youre interested in setting up WordPress in the cloud, Sarah Gooding shows you<a href="http://wptavern.com/wordpress-in-the-cloud-how-to-set-up-a-development-site-with-koding" target="_blank">how to do it with Koding</a>,online development environment where you can create and run apps in the cloud.</p>\n<p><strong>Random awesomeness.</strong>Many people are stingy when it comes to raising money for charity, but<a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/324283889/potato-salad" target="_blank">this guy has managed to raise more than $30,000</a>in four days to make<a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/324283889/potato-salad" target="_blank">potato salad</a>. Elsewhere, a New Zealand ISP<a href="http://gigaom.com/2014/07/07/new-zealand-isp-allows-its-customers-to-subscribe-to-the-u-s-version-of-netflix/" target="_blank">has found a cheeky way</a>to allow it customers to subscribe to Netflix. Plus,<a href="http://www.hongkiat.com/blog/amazing-prosthetic-limbs-organs/" target="_blank">amazing prosthetics that make people part human, part robot</a>.</p>\n<p>Hope you have a brilliant day!</p>\n<div class=''yarpp-related-rss''>\n<p>Related posts:</p><ol>\n<li><a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/the-whip-newsletter-21/" rel="bookmark" title="The WhiP Newsletter #21">The WhiP Newsletter #21 </a> <small>Daily lashings of WordPress goodness....</small></li>\n<li><a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/the-whip-newsletters-36/" rel="bookmark" title="The WhiP Newsletters #36">The WhiP Newsletters #36 </a> <small>Obox launches hosting service, WooCommerceCamp announced, and theme builders allow...</small></li>\n<li><a href="http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/the-whip-newsletters-34/" rel="bookmark" title="The WhiP Newsletters #34">The WhiP Newsletters #34 </a> <small>What secret projects is Automattic working on? And lots of...</small></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/the-whip-newletter-37/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"href";s:54:"http://premium.wpmudev.org/blog/category/wpmudev/feed/";s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:"type";i:128;s:7:"headers";a:11:{s:4:"date";s:29:"Thu, 28 Aug 2014 07:08:26 GMT";s:12:"content-type";s:24:"text/html; charset=UTF-8";s:10:"connection";s:5:"close";s:10:"set-cookie";s:133:"__cfduid=d97a19ee8b74766c1fe0db7c73ec4b94b1409209706619; expires=Mon, 23-Dec-2019 23:50:00 GMT; path=/; domain=.wpmudev.org; HttpOnly";s:4:"vary";s:6:"Cookie";s:13:"last-modified";s:31:"Thu, 28 Aug 2014 07:03:59 +0000";s:13:"cache-control";s:27:"max-age=33, must-revalidate";s:10:"cf-railgun";s:27:"00b15a7f2a 0010 normal 5360";s:6:"server";s:16:"cloudflare-nginx";s:6:"cf-ray";s:20:"160ead7a5a9f03be-SIN";s:16:"content-encoding";s:4:"gzip";}s:5:"build";s:14:"20140811053142";}', 'no');
